This paper presents a probabilistic model for clustering relational data, which is a common problem in machine learning and data science. The paper focuses on developing efficient and practical inference methods for the model, which is a key concern in the subfield of probabilistic modeling and Bayesian inference. The paper uses techniques such as variational inference and Dirichlet processes, which are commonly used in machine learning and Bayesian statistics. Based on these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.DB (Databases).
